<subSubSection pageNumber="608" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="608">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Note:</emphasis>
Many authors including Fernald (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Rhodora</emphasis>
42: 53. 1940), Lawrence (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Baileya</emphasis>
1: 64. 1953), Southall &amp; Hardin (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">J. Elisha Mitch. Sci. Soc.</emphasis>
90: 16. 1974), Reveal &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Huntia</emphasis>
7: 219. 1987) regarded the name as partially or wholly based on 
<specimenReference collectionCode="LINN" specimenCode="560.1">
Herb. Linn. 560.1 (
<collectionCode>LINN</collectionCode>
)
</specimenReference>
, and Ebinger (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Rhodora</emphasis>
76: 352. 1974) explicitly restricted the type to the top right-hand specimen on the sheet. However, the sheet lacks a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">
<volumeTitle>Species Plantarum</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
number and is a post-1753 addition to the collection and hence ineligible as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
. Annotations by Kalm on a sheet collected by him, and now in UPS, are reproduced by Lundqvist &amp; Moberg (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="608">Thunbergia</emphasis>
19: 7, f. 3. 1993).
</paragraph>
